<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="pink">
    <script>
        var x=100;
        if(x > 90){
            document.write('Yes The value of x is'+x+'<br>')
        }
        document.write('Hello')
    </script>
</body>
</html>

Result: 
-------
Yes The value of x is:100
Hello

Note: Here IF Statement is a conditional statement when the given condition is true at that time only it prints otherwise it terminates from that condition
      and check the other condition


